
Local fix for vkd3d-shader signature mismatch abort, hit by Affinity Photo 3
text/UI draw calls under wined3d's Vulkan backend (NOT vkd3d-proton/D3D12,
this is wined3d's own D3D9/10/11 shader translation path, libs/vkd3d-shader).

Confirmed still unfixed as of vkd3d release 1.14 (latest tag checked).

vsir_program_remap_output_signature() aborts compilation whenever a later
shader stage's input mask reads components an earlier stage's output mask
never wrote ("Input mask 0xf reads components not written in output mask
0x3"). Real D3D drivers tolerate this and simply read back zero for the
unwritten components. This patch does the same: widens the signature
element's mask to cover what's read, and synthesizes zero-writes for the
missing components before every ret, reusing the same technique the
function already uses just below for entirely-uninitialized varyings.

Compile-checked with gcc -fsyntax-only against this tree's generated
config.h; NOT runtime-tested against an actual Vulkan device. Build it,
run with WINEDEBUG=+d3d_shader,+d3d and confirm the
"Input mask ... reads components not written" abort is gone and the
glyph/text draw calls succeed before relying on this.

